HEADWORD: Phrenic
<hw>Phren"ic</hw> <pr>(fr⟦ecr⟧n"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>frh`n</grk>, <grk>freno`s</grk>, the midriff, or diaphragm, the
heart, the mind: cf. F. <ets>phr⟦eacute⟧nique</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the diaphragm;
diaphragmatic; <as>as, the <ex>phrenic</ex> nerve</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

